---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { formatPostDate } from '../data/format';
import { frontmatter as post } from '../content/posts/system-design-of-search-engine.md';
---
<BaseLayout title="Blog" description="Posts on engineering, learning systems, and ideas.">
  <div class="page-heading">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Home</a>
    <h1>Blog</h1>
    <p>"Your brain is for having ideas, not holding them." - David Allen</p>
  </div>

  <div class="feed-list">
    <article class="notelist-feed">
      <a href="/posts/system-design-of-search-engine">
        <div class="home-post-meta">
          <span class="feed-type-post">Post</span>
          <time datetime={new Date(post.date).toISOString()}>{formatPostDate(post.date)}</time>
        </div>
        <h2>{post.title}</h2>
        <p class="excerpt">
          Search looks simple from the outside: type a query, get ten blue links. Under the hood it is one of the most interesting large-scale system design problems.
        </p>
      </a>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
